<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<div tal:replace="nothing">
  This page uses the launchpad-form.pt METAL. Copy this page to your
  object-form.pt and then tweak the various bits below to make it all look
  nice.
</div>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-actions" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_generalform/generalform">

    <h1 tal:condition="view/label"
        tal:content="view/label"
        metal:fill-slot="heading">Heading from ZCML label="xxx"</h1>

    <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info" class="documentDescription">
      Please the introductory paragraph here. It will be displayed in
      bold text below the form title. It should be a single paragraph
      giving an overview of what is being added.
    </div>

    <div class="row" metal:fill-slot="extra_top" tal:replace="nothing">
      <div class="label">Extra top</div>
      <div class="label"><input type="text" style="width:100%" /></div>
      <div>
        Put any extra form elements you want for this form which
        are not autogenerated here, and they will be at the top of the
        form. The auto-generated elements will use the layout from
        launchpad-widget-macros.pt so try to follow that pattern.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" metal:fill-slot="extra_bottom" tal:replace="nothing">
      <div class="label">Extra bottom</div>
      <div class="field"><input type="text" style="width:100%" /></div>
      <div>
        If you want additional non-autogenerated widgets on the firm,
        add them here, as for the set above.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" metal:fill-slot="extra_buttons" tal:replace="nothing">
      If you wish to add some more buttons to the form, put those here.
    </div>

  </div>

  <div tal:replace="nothing">
    This piece will appear at the bottom of the form if you want to add
    a footer.
  </div>

</div>
    
</body>
</html>

